    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nstreecontroller"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " class provides selection and sort management. Its primary purpose is to act as the controller when binding "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nsoutlineview"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " and "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nsbrowser"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " instances to a hierarchical collection of objects. The root content object of the tree can be a single object, or an array of objects."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "An "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nstreecontroller"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " object requires that you describe how the tree of objects is traversed by specifying the key-path for child objects specified by "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nstreecontroller/1528721-childrenkeypath"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ". All child objects for the tree must be key-value coding compliant for the same child key path. If necessary, you should add properties to your model classes that map the child key name to the appropriate class-specific property name."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Child objects can implement a count method (specified to the tree controller using "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nstreecontroller/1529127-countkeypath"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ") that, if provided, returns the number of child objects available. Your model objects are expected to update the value of the count key path in a key-value observing compliant method. Optionally, you can also provide a leaf key path using "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nstreecontroller/1532164-leafkeypath"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " that specifies a key in your model object that returns "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/objectivec/yes"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " if the object is a leaf node, and "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/objectivec/no"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " if it is not. Changes to the leaf node value of the child object should be made in a key-value observing compliant manner. Providing the leaf node key path can improve performance, because it prevents the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nstreecontroller"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " from having to examine the child object to determine if it is a leaf node."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "For more information about using NSTreeController in your app, see "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/cocoa_bindings/navigating_hierarchical_data_using_outline_and_split_views"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
